  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-04-28",
    "date": "2021-06-23T18:56:12Z",
    "text": "Clean Slate Act of 2021\n\nThis bill establishes a framework for sealing records related to certain federal criminal offenses.\n\nCourts must automatically seal records related to (1) a conviction for simple possession of a controlled substance or for any nonviolent offense involving marijuana, or (2) an arrest for an offense that does not result in a conviction.\n\nAdditionally, an individual who meets certain criteria may petition to seal records related to a conviction for other nonviolent offenses."
  },
